label: ABC_oC12_63_c_c_c-004
title: UBC Structure
comments:
(Rogl, 1993) found that excess carbon could replace boron, and that some uranium atoms could be replaced by scandium, lutetium, or thorium. 
 See the note on the \href{current_web_home_dir/ABC_oC12_63_c_c_c-005}{MoAlB} structure page concerning the relationship between this structure and other structures with the ABC\_oC12\_63\_c\_c\_c label.
